    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-16T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1160"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1160">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/11–1649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-16T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 16, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 16—2:11 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4804. ReDeptel 2271. Pattison Company, Isbrandtsen agent, has radioed Master <hi
                        rend="italic">Flying Cloud</hi> for details. Will reply soonest. British <hi
                        rend="italic">Wosang</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Tsinan</hi>, held in Yangtze
                    territorial waters, released by Chinese gunboat and sailed for Hong Kong
                    November 16. Local company offices unaware reason for release. Norwegian <hi
                        rend="italic">Promise</hi>, food gone, gave up attempt enter and sailed for
                    Tsingtao November 15. Greek <hi rend="italic">Armathia</hi> previously held
                    Chusan Island reported arrived Hong Kong November 14.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
